## Design Rationale

| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Self-contained** | Inline stub lets the file run before production code exists; replace the `try/except` import block once real modules ship. |
| **Boundary strategy** | Every numeric threshold tested at **exact value**, **one unit below**, and **one unit above** (classic boundary-value analysis). |
| **Ownership restriction** | All four ownership-mutation operations tested individually for the secondary holder; primary-holder positive cases confirm the guard is role-specific, not blanket. |
| **Test isolation** | Each test receives fresh objects via fixtures; no shared mutable state between tests. |
| **Parametrisation** | Cross-role tests use `@pytest.mark.parametrize` + `request.getfixturevalue` to run identical scenarios for both holders without duplication. |
| **Audit / integrity** | Failed transactions must neither alter the balance nor appear in history — both are explicitly asserted. |
| **Precision** | `Decimal` used throughout to prevent floating-point drift in financial assertions. |
